Package TicTacToe

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Agent  
    AggressiveAgent
    An aggressive agent: if there is a winning move, this agent always plays it.
    AggressivePolicy
    An agrgessive policy: if there is a winning move given a game state (Game object) then this policy finds it.
    DefensiveAgent
    A defensive agent: if there is a move to block the opponent this agent will play it.
    DefensivePolicy
    A defensive policy: if there is a move to block the opponent's X's or O's in a row, this policy finds it and returns it.
    EpsilonGreedyPolicy
    to do for next year
    Game
    This is a class that defines the environment of a Tic Tac Toe Game: its underlying state representation, actions transitions etc.
    HumanAgent
    A human agent that doesn't have a policy, instead asks the user to enter a move using a command line.
    IndexPair  
    Move
    A move in the Tic-Tac-Toe game.
    Outcome
    This is a game outcome: a data structure containing a game (state), a move, a reward, and the next target game state.
    Policy
    A Tic Tac Toe Policy implemented via a HashMap
    PolicyIterationAgent
    A policy iteration agent.
    QLearningAgent
    A Q-Learning agent with a Q table, i.e.
    RandomAgent
    A random agent, i.e.
    RandomPolicy
    This is a Policy which picks an move randomly with equal probability from the available moves.
    TransitionProb
    A tuple containing an Outcome object, with its associated probability - this specifies the probability of the transition occurring.
    TTTEnvironment
    This is a Reinforcement Learning environment for Tic Tac Toe.
    TTTMDP
    This class specifies a full MDP for the Tic Tac Toe game, i.e.
    ValueIterationAgent
    A Value Iteration Agent, only very partially implemented.
